# Shell scripts are executed inside Linux containers (bind-mounted or
# COPY'd verbatim) - a CRLF line ending corrupts the shebang line
# (`#!/bin/sh` becomes `#!/bin/sh\r`, "bad interpreter: No such file or
# directory") and breaks the script entirely. Force LF regardless of the
# checkout platform's core.autocrlf setting.
*.sh text eol=lf
